value.0:
*As you approach, the woman looks up at you. Her eyes are red and she has clearly been weeping.*

Yes?

*She sighs.*

Go ahead.
I don't know much about that. Speak to Burgomaster Bors in Osthavn. He might be able to tell you more.

Ostdur is the capital of the Jarldom of Ostland. Just head north until you get to the crossroads, then turn left and head straight into the mountains. The fortress itself blocks the pass up to Huyslod.

That's the capital of Ruathym, sort of. It used to be Holgerstead, in the jarldom of Ottar to the south, but when the First Axe Aumark Lithyl died, oh, about ten years ago I think it was, his son Thorden moved the court up to Huyslod.
They dress in rags and feathers. You can hear them, sometimes, at night, making strange noises. It's eerie - like insane flutes or something.
I have crafted a charm of feathers and bird bones and other things that keeps them away.

Mm hm. There is a fruit called the maroela, which grows on a rare tree that bears pink leaves all year round. If the seeds are eaten, you sicken and die, but in the mean time it drives you mad. I have used them in my charm.

They're the personal guard of the Axe, Raorik Bathrie, curse his name. They show no mercy to anyone they think might be breaking the Axe's law. It's said that people who go into the dungeons of Ostdur almost never return.

No, they can't. They work for the Burgomaster and only keep order in town. He's responsible to the Axe himself and can't go against the Knights. 

They're not very popular in Osthavn, but there isn't much anyone can do without 'going to Ostdur' themselves.
Have you done what I asked of you?

Comment.value: PC receives a potion of heal and 1500 xp total for the quest

value.0: I thank you for your service, stranger. I can't offer you any coin, but take this. Perhaps it will be of help to you.
Also, I do not know what is happening in Ostdur, but I advise you to be careful what you say or the Everwatch Knights may come for you as well.
Have you done what I asked of you?
Go, and do not return until you have given my daughter the potion and the message.
Quickly! Give me the flesh of the leech that I sent you to the swamp for!
I will make a potion for you that you must give to my daughter. Tell her that it will release her from her prison and her pain, and that I love her.
Don't ask questions. Just do as I say.

*She vanishes into the house and returns a few moments later, handing you a potion bottle.*

Go! Now!
Give me the flesh of the leech that I sent you to the swamp for!
Go, quickly! Bring it to me!
Oh, <sir/madam>! Give me the news of my poor daughter's fate!
You must tell me all!

*Her expression becomes hard and her eyes glitter with fury.*

You're right. But whatever it is, it can't be good.

You must do me another favor, then. Go up the road a ways and you will enter the northern part of the Frygtmere, a cold and dismal swamp. Deep within it you will find giant leeches bigger than a man, whose bite will drain you dry if you do not treat the wound quickly. If you bring me the gland from the mouth of one, I will make a potion that will release my daughter and foil whatever evil plot the fiends of Ostdur have planned for her blood.

*She glares at you.*

Go now and do this thing for me or I shall curse you as I shall curse the Axe Bathrie and all who infest the rotten bones of the fortress of Ostdur.
You tempt my vengeance. Be wary!
Oh, thank the gods you're back! Did you find out anything about my daughter?
Just head north until you get to the crossroads, then turn left and head straight into the mountains. The fortress of Ostdur blocks the pass up to Huyslod.

That's the capital of Ostland, sort of. It used to be Holgerstead, in the jarldom of Ottar to the south, but when the First Axe Aumark Lithyl died, oh, about ten years ago I think it was, his son Thorden moved the court up to Huyslod.

*As you approach, the woman looks up at you. Her eyes are red and she has clearly been weeping.*

Yes?
My daughter's gone missing. I heard from a neighbor she was taken to Ostdur by the Everwatch Knights when she went to market in town.

*She sighs.*

I understand. I guess it was too much to expect.

*She turns away, her head bowed in sorrow.*
If you could at least go to Ostdur and ask after her, that'd be... well... at least I'd know what happened. Still, I'd almost rather she'd been taken by a bear, or those crazy bandits in the woods...

Thank you so much, <sir/madam>. It would mean so much to me.

*She turns away, her head bowed in sorrow.*
What do you want to know?
I don't know anything about that. Speak to Burgomaster Bors in Osthavn. He might be able to tell you more.

They dress in rags and feathers. You can hear them, sometimes, at night, making strange noises. It's eerie - like insane flutes or something. They don't have anything to do with the Everwatch Knights, though.
I have crafted a charm of feathers and bird bones and other things that keeps them away.

Mm hm. There is a fruit called the maroela, which grows on a rare tree that bears pink leaves all year round. If the seeds are eaten, you sicken and die, but in the mean time it drives you mad. I have used them in my charm.

I've been up there once or twice. Sometimes the cells in the dungeons have little windows in the outside walls of the keep. That's about all I can think of. I'd really like to know if she's there, <sir/madam>. I'm sure you understand.

They're the personal guard of the Axe, Raorik Bathrie, curse his name. They show no mercy to anyone they think might be breaking the Axe's law. It's said that people who go into the dungeons of Ostdur almost never return.
Just head north until you get to the crossroads, then turn left and head straight into the mountains. The fortress of Ostdur blocks the pass up to Huyslod.

That's the capital of Ruathym, sort of. It used to be Holgerstead, in the jarldom of Ottar to the south, but when the First Axe Aumark Lithyl died, oh, about ten years ago I think it was, his son Thorden moved the court up to Huyslod.

No, they can't. They work for the Burgomaster and only keep order in town. He's responsible to the Axe himself and can't go against the Knights. 

They're not very popular in Osthavn, but there isn't much anyone can do without 'going to Ostdur' themselves.
I'm sorry to bother you, but can I ask you some questions?
Never mind. I can see you're upset. I won't trouble you right now.
What can you tell me about the history of Ostland?
Thank you. I won't trouble you any more right now.
I see. Thank you. Can I ask you something else?
What can you tell me about Ostdur?
Now I'm confused. What's Huyslod?
Thanks very much for the information.
I see. Do you mind if I ask you some more questions?
What can you tell me about the bandits in the woods across the road, there?
Why don't they bother you?
Other things?
Thanks very much for the information.
That's very interesting. Do you mind if I ask you some more questions?
What can you tell me about the Everwatch Knights?
The guards in Osthavn don't stop them?
Thanks very much for the information.
Do you mind if I ask you some more questions?
I did. Your daughter took the potion and said she loved you as well.
Thank you. I will keep that in mind.
I appreciate the advice. Good <day/night> to you, madam.
Nope.
I'm going, I'm going!
Here you go. It wasn't easy to get!
What will it do?
Whatever you say, lady.
I'm on my way.
No way. I have no idea what craziness you're up to.
I don't have it yet.
You got it! Right away, ma'am!
I found her in the dungeons of Ostdur I spoke to her through a tiny cell window, and she told me that... well... it's not a pretty tale...

It seems that the jailers have been draining the blood of those in the dungeons, a bit at a time, until... until they can't, anymore. The prisoners don't know why, but all sorts of unpleasant things come to mind.
I fear you are correct about that.
I'm on my way!
Hey, I didn't sign up for this, lady. I only agreed to find out what happened to your daughter.
I'm on my way!
I'll think about it.
I'm on my way!
No way! I'm outta here.
Not yet. But can you tell me how to get to Ostdur again?
Ah, yes, thanks.
What's Huyslod?
Ah, yes, thanks.
Not yet, madam. But I'll let you know as soon as I get back from Ostdur.
What's wrong?
Sorry, lady, but I'm not messing with the Everwatch Knights.
Yeah, well... I'll just be going now...
Perhaps I can find your daughter for you, ma'am!
All right. I'll see what I can do for you.
I'll be back as soon as I can.
I'll need some more information, though.
I'm sorry to hear that. I'm not sure how I can help, though. I'd definitely need some more information.
Can you tell me anything about the history of Ostland?
Thank you for the information. But I'll need to know more, I think, to be able to help you.
What can you tell me about the bandits in the woods across the road, there?
Why don't they bother you?
Other things?
That's a very interesting story. I'll need some more information, though, if I'm going to help find your daughter.
How would I find your daughter when I get to Ostdur? I don't think the Everwatch Knights will just let me walk right in and ask questions, will they?
I'll need some more information.
What can you tell me about the Everwatch Knights?
How would I get to Ostdur? Assuming I agreed to go, I mean.
Now I'm confused. What's Huyslod?
I see. Now, the guards in Osthavn don't stop the Everwatch Knights from just taking people away?
Ah, I understand now. But I'll need some more information if I'm going to help you.
The guards in Osthavn don't stop them?
I see. I'll need some more information, though.
